<center><i>Valas Defai,<a href=http://www.triadcontinuum.com>Triad Continuum</a> </i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubaelzharon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baelzharon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/31/01 8:54:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.plauder-smilies.de/rough/headshot.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell casting Mastery of Fury</span><hr size=1> Heh I got my first point into Casting Fury Friday night and already while on raids when a nuke crits its funny. All the tanks are like &quot;Ohhh woooowww!!&quot; and &quot;OMG Bael!! did 1800!!&quot;. IMHO our damage wasn't really the problem, and we deal out a considerable amount too. The problem is the perception that we don't do anything, and finally getting that recognition over the weekend was well worth 8 AA points I've spent getting there.<br>
